Note:
==============================================================================
QUERY_AST - Generic Relational Query AST (substrate for SQL / RQL)
==============================================================================

The shared AST for all relational query dialects.  SQL, RQL, and any
other relational language that targets this substrate produces and
consumes nodes defined here.  Coverage mirrors the SQL:2016 standard's
SELECT statement structure (ISO/IEC 9075-2:2016) plus DML and DDL
infrastructure.

Top-level node kinds:

  Q_SELECT        SELECT statement (clauses below)
  Q_INSERT        INSERT statement
  Q_UPDATE        UPDATE statement
  Q_DELETE        DELETE statement
  Q_UNION         set operation
  Q_INTERSECT     set operation
  Q_EXCEPT        set operation

Clause kinds (children of Q_SELECT):

  Q_SELECT_LIST   list of projection expressions / column references
  Q_FROM          list of tables/joins
  Q_WHERE         predicate expression
  Q_GROUP_BY      list of grouping expressions
  Q_HAVING        predicate expression
  Q_ORDER_BY      list of (expression, direction) pairs
  Q_LIMIT         numeric limit
  Q_OFFSET        numeric offset
  Q_JOIN          join (kind, table, ON predicate)

Expression kinds:

  Q_COLUMN        column reference - primary stores name, secondary stores table alias
  Q_LITERAL       literal value - secondary stores literal type (INT/STR/FLOAT/BOOL/NULL)
  Q_BINOP         binary op - primary stores operator string, children = [lhs, rhs]
  Q_UNARYOP       unary op
  Q_FUNCALL       function call - primary stores name, children = arguments
  Q_SUBQUERY      nested query - primary 0, children = [subquery_root]
  Q_CASE          CASE expression - children = [when, then, when, then, ..., else]
  Q_CAST          CAST(expr AS type) - primary = type name, children = [expr]

Predicate kinds (subset of expressions):

  Q_CMP           comparison op
  Q_LOGICAL       AND/OR/NOT
  Q_IN_LIST       expr IN (val1, val2, ...)
  Q_IN_SUBQUERY   expr IN (subquery)
  Q_BETWEEN       expr BETWEEN lo AND hi
  Q_LIKE          expr LIKE pattern
  Q_IS_NULL       expr IS NULL
  Q_EXISTS        EXISTS(subquery)

Node record layout (40 bytes, tagged variant):

  off  0  kind tag       Q_*
  off  8  primary str    name / operator / type
  off 16  secondary      auxiliary integer / pointer (literal_type, direction, ...)
  off 24  children list  List of child nodes / clause nodes
  off 32  payload        for Q_LITERAL: the boxed value (String / Integer)

References:
  - SQL:2016: ISO/IEC 9075:2016
  - PostgreSQL grammar https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/sql-syntax.html
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NODE KIND TAGS
Note: ============================================================================

Constant Q_SELECT as Integer is 1
Constant Q_INSERT as Integer is 2
Constant Q_UPDATE as Integer is 3
Constant Q_DELETE as Integer is 4
Constant Q_UNION as Integer is 5
Constant Q_INTERSECT as Integer is 6
Constant Q_EXCEPT as Integer is 7

Constant Q_SELECT_LIST as Integer is 10
Constant Q_FROM as Integer is 11
Constant Q_WHERE as Integer is 12
Constant Q_GROUP_BY as Integer is 13
Constant Q_HAVING as Integer is 14
Constant Q_ORDER_BY as Integer is 15
Constant Q_LIMIT as Integer is 16
Constant Q_OFFSET as Integer is 17
Constant Q_JOIN as Integer is 18

Constant Q_COLUMN as Integer is 20
Constant Q_LITERAL as Integer is 21
Constant Q_BINOP as Integer is 22
Constant Q_UNARYOP as Integer is 23
Constant Q_FUNCALL as Integer is 24
Constant Q_SUBQUERY as Integer is 25
Constant Q_CASE as Integer is 26
Constant Q_CAST as Integer is 27

Constant Q_CMP as Integer is 30
Constant Q_LOGICAL as Integer is 31
Constant Q_IN_LIST as Integer is 32
Constant Q_IN_SUBQUERY as Integer is 33
Constant Q_BETWEEN as Integer is 34
Constant Q_LIKE as Integer is 35
Constant Q_IS_NULL as Integer is 36
Constant Q_EXISTS as Integer is 37

Constant Q_ORDER_ASC as Integer is 0
Constant Q_ORDER_DESC as Integer is 1

Constant Q_JOIN_INNER as Integer is 0
Constant Q_JOIN_LEFT as Integer is 1
Constant Q_JOIN_RIGHT as Integer is 2
Constant Q_JOIN_FULL as Integer is 3
Constant Q_JOIN_CROSS as Integer is 4

Constant Q_LIT_INTEGER as Integer is 0
Constant Q_LIT_FLOAT as Integer is 1
Constant Q_LIT_STRING as Integer is 2
Constant Q_LIT_BOOL as Integer is 3
Constant Q_LIT_NULL as Integer is 4

Constant Q_NODE_SIZE as Integer is 40
Constant Q_OFF_KIND as Integer is 0
Constant Q_OFF_PRIMARY as Integer is 8
Constant Q_OFF_SECONDARY as Integer is 16
Constant Q_OFF_CHILDREN as Integer is 24
Constant Q_OFF_PAYLOAD as Integer is 32

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NODE CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a 40-byte query AST node with kind tag, primary/secondary
slots, and a freshly allocated empty child List.  Caller is
responsible for populating children with query_ast_add_child.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Two Layout.allocate calls (node + list); on OOM, deallocate the node
and return 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "query_ast_create" takes kind as Integer, primary as Integer, secondary as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with Q_NODE_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc list_create from List
    If children is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with record
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, Q_OFF_KIND, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, Q_OFF_PRIMARY, primary
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, Q_OFF_SECONDARY, secondary
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, Q_OFF_CHILDREN, children
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, Q_OFF_PAYLOAD, 0
    Return record
End Process

Process called "query_ast_get_kind" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_KIND
End Process

Process called "query_ast_get_primary" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_PRIMARY
End Process

Process called "query_ast_get_secondary" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_SECONDARY
End Process

Process called "query_ast_get_children" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_CHILDREN
End Process

Process called "query_ast_get_payload" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_PAYLOAD
End Process

Process called "query_ast_set_payload" takes node as Integer, payload as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_PAYLOAD, payload
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "query_ast_add_child" takes parent as Integer, child as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parent, Q_OFF_CHILDREN
    Return proc list_push from List with children, child
End Process

Process called "query_ast_child_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_CHILDREN
    Return proc list_length from List with children
End Process

Process called "query_ast_get_child" takes node as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_CHILDREN
    Let count be proc list_length from List with children
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to count:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc list_get from List with children, index
End Process

@Reasoning
Locate the first child clause with the requested kind (one of the
Q_SELECT_LIST, Q_FROM, Q_WHERE, ... constants).  Used by serializers
and planners to pull specific clauses out of a SELECT node.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Linear scan of the children list.  Returns 0 if no such clause.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(child count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "query_ast_find_clause" takes node as Integer, clause_kind as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_CHILDREN
    Let count be proc list_length from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let c be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let k be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, Q_OFF_KIND
        If k is equal to clause_kind:
            Return c
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONVENIENCE CONSTRUCTORS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "qa_column" takes name as Integer, table_alias as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc query_ast_create with Q_COLUMN, name, table_alias
End Process

Process called "qa_literal_integer" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc query_ast_create with Q_LITERAL, 0, Q_LIT_INTEGER
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc query_ast_set_payload with node, value
    Return node
End Process

Process called "qa_literal_string" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc query_ast_create with Q_LITERAL, text, Q_LIT_STRING
    Return node
End Process

Process called "qa_literal_bool" takes flag as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc query_ast_create with Q_LITERAL, 0, Q_LIT_BOOL
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc query_ast_set_payload with node, flag
    Return node
End Process

Process called "qa_literal_null" returns Integer:
    Return proc query_ast_create with Q_LITERAL, 0, Q_LIT_NULL
End Process

Process called "qa_binop" takes op as Integer, lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc query_ast_create with Q_BINOP, op, 0
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc query_ast_add_child with node, lhs
    proc query_ast_add_child with node, rhs
    Return node
End Process

Process called "qa_cmp" takes op as Integer, lhs as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc query_ast_create with Q_CMP, op, 0
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc query_ast_add_child with node, lhs
    proc query_ast_add_child with node, rhs
    Return node
End Process

Process called "qa_funcall" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc query_ast_create with Q_FUNCALL, name, 0
End Process

Process called "qa_select" returns Integer:
    Return proc query_ast_create with Q_SELECT, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "qa_clause" takes kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc query_ast_create with kind, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "qa_order_item" takes expr as Integer, direction as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc query_ast_create with Q_ORDER_BY, 0, direction
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc query_ast_add_child with node, expr
    Return node
End Process

Process called "qa_join" takes table_name as Integer, kind as Integer, on_pred as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc query_ast_create with Q_JOIN, table_name, kind
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If on_pred is not equal to 0:
        proc query_ast_add_child with node, on_pred
    End If
    Return node
End Process

Process called "qa_limit" takes count as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc query_ast_create with Q_LIMIT, 0, count
    Return node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WALK
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Depth-first pre-order traversal.  Populates the supplied out list with
every reachable node in the AST.  Visitor pattern equivalent: callers
that need conditional dispatch can pre-filter the populated list.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Iterative two-stack DFS with the work-list bounded by tree size.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(node count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns negative on null inputs.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "query_ast_walk" takes root as Integer, out_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    If out_list is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Let stack be proc list_create from List
    If stack is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    proc list_push from List with stack, root
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let len be proc list_length from List with stack
        If len is equal to 0:
            proc list_destroy from List with stack
            Return 0
        End If
        Let top be len minus 1
        Let cur be proc list_get from List with stack, top
        proc list_remove from List with stack, top
        proc list_push from List with out_list, cur
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, Q_OFF_CHILDREN
        If children is not equal to 0:
            Let cc be proc list_length from List with children
            Let i be cc minus 1
            While i is greater than or equal to 0:
                Let c be proc list_get from List with children, i
                If c is not equal to 0:
                    proc list_push from List with stack, c
                End If
                Set i to i minus 1
            End While
        End If
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with stack
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DESTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Recursively destroy a query AST node and every descendant.  String
payloads are caller-owned.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
For each child invoke query_ast_destroy recursively, destroy the
backing list, free the record.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(total node count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "query_ast_destroy" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_CHILDREN
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let count be proc list_length from List with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let c be proc list_get from List with children, i
            proc query_ast_destroy with c
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with children
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with node
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PRETTY PRINTER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Render the AST to a human-readable string.  Used by EXPLAIN-like
tooling and diagnostics.  Renders each clause on its own line with a
short symbolic prefix.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Recursive walker writing into a StringBuilder.  Each node kind has a
custom serialization snippet.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(tree size + total string length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "qa_append_indent" takes sb as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Let i be 0
    Let total be level multiplied by 2
    While i is less than total:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 32
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "qa_render" takes sb as Integer, node as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_KIND
    Let primary be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_PRIMARY
    proc qa_append_indent with sb, level
    If kind is equal to Q_SELECT:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "SELECT"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_SELECT_LIST:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "select_list"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_FROM:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "FROM"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_WHERE:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "WHERE"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_GROUP_BY:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "GROUP BY"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_HAVING:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "HAVING"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_ORDER_BY:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "ORDER BY"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_LIMIT:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "LIMIT "
        Let limit_n be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_SECONDARY
        proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, limit_n
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_OFFSET:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "OFFSET "
        Let off_n be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_SECONDARY
        proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, off_n
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_JOIN:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "JOIN "
        If primary is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, primary
        End If
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_COLUMN:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "column("
        If primary is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, primary
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ")"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_LITERAL:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "literal("
        Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_PAYLOAD
        Let secondary be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_SECONDARY
        If secondary is equal to Q_LIT_INTEGER:
            proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, payload
        Otherwise:
            If primary is not equal to 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, primary
            End If
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ")"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_BINOP:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "binop("
        If primary is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, primary
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ")"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_CMP:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "cmp("
        If primary is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, primary
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ")"
    End If
    If kind is equal to Q_FUNCALL:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "call "
        If primary is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, primary
        End If
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
    Let cs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, Q_OFF_CHILDREN
    If cs is not equal to 0:
        Let cc be proc list_length from List with cs
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than cc:
            Let cn be proc list_get from List with cs, i
            proc qa_render with sb, cn, level plus 1
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "query_ast_to_string" takes root as Integer returns Integer:
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc qa_render with sb, root, 0
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process
